name: Anti5ix5even
description: No more of that pesky number, or either of its digits.

tolerable-header.name: Tolerable Settings
tolerable-header.description: These are the settings that could you could get away with leaving enabled without too much of a headache. They're enabled by default.

noLevelsContainingName.name: Auto-Kick from Levels With Names Referencing The Two Digits
noLevelsContainingName.description: Prevents you from playing levels whose names make *even the* ***__slightest__*** reference to either of The Two Digits.

noLevelListsContainingName.name: Auto-Kick from Level Lists With Names Referencing The Two Digits
noLevelListsContainingName.description: Prevents you from viewing level lists whose names make *even the* ***__slightest__*** reference to either of The Two Digits.

noHarderLevels.name: Auto-Kick from Rated Harder Levels
noHarderLevels.description:
Prevents you from playing rated Harder levels.

<cy>You know ***__very__*** well why.</c>

noHarderLevelsInsideLevelLists.name: Auto-Kick from Level Lists with Rated Harder Levels
noHarderLevelsInsideLevelLists.description:
Prevents you from viewing level lists with rated Harder levels.

<cy>You know ***__very__*** well why.</c>

noOffendingIcons.name: Auto-Kick from Levels If Any Gamemode's Current Icon Number References The Two Digits

noOffendingLevelsWithOffendingTextObject.name: Auto-Kick from Levels Containing Text Objects Referring To The Two Digits
noOffendingLevelsWithOffendingTextObject.description: Prevents you from playing levels containing text objects that make *even the* ***__slightest__*** reference to either of The Two Digits.

noOffendingLevelIDsConsecutively.name: Auto-Kick from Levels whose IDs Contain Both Of The Two Digits Consecutively
noOffendingLevelIDsConsecutively.description:
Prevents you from playing levels whose Level IDs contain The Two Digits consecutively. Notable examples include:
- <cr>CraZy</c> by DavJT
- <cg>Because I Loved Her</c> by Jayuff
- <cl>Moving Obstacles</c> by Sumsar
- <cy>Polargeist X</c> by SpacePark
- <co>Danger Zone</c> by GD Jose
- <cg>stereo madness v2</c> by IIINePtunEIII
- <co>Aquarius</c> by Skitten
- <cy>Moonlight</c> by Unzor

noOffendingLevelIDsIndividually.name: Auto-Kick from Levels whose IDs Contain Both Of The Two Digits Individually
noOffendingLevelIDsIndividually.description:
Prevents you from playing levels whose Level IDs contain both of The Two Digits, but not consecutively. Notable examples include:
- <cr>Bloodbath</c> by Riot and more
- <cl>Promises</c> by Adiale
- <cg>Chambers</c> by SirHadoken
- <cg>through time</c> by Berkoo

noOffendingLevelIDsExclusiveOr.name: Auto-Kick from Levels whose IDs Contain Either Of The Two Digits
noOffendingLevelIDsExclusiveOr.description:
Prevents you from playing levels whose Level IDs contain ***__ONLY__*** one of The Two Digits. Notable examples include:
- <cl>ReTraY</c> by DiMaViKuLov26
- <co>First Race</c> by Stamina
- <cr>X</c> by TriAxis and TamaN
- <cy>Almighty</c> by aArbolito
- <ca>Unity</c> by TriAxis and FunnyGame
- <cy>dorabaebasic5</c> by DORABAE
- <cg>LETs GO</c> by izhar
- <co>SLAM</c> by rafer

noOffendingLevelListIDsConsecutively.name: Auto-Kick from Level Lists whose IDs Contain Both Of The Two Digits Consecutively
noOffendingLevelListIDsConsecutively.description:
Prevents you from viewing level lists whose Level IDs contain The Two Digits consecutively. Notable examples include:
- <cr>Best modern level</c> by Kataslysis
- <cy>Five of a Kind</c> by qKitti
- <cr>The Towerverse Story</c> by 16lord
- <cr>Take Two</c> by xXLOCOXx
- <cg>Find The Wubba Ducks</c> by GiggsRH
- <c-AAAAAA>Prediction Gauntlet</c> by TwisterDude161
- <cy>Learn Your Opposites</c> by sink
- <ca>The Team Zero Catalogue</c> by Infra
- <cr>certified bangers</c> by nasgubb
- <co>Peak Platformers</c> by Colon

noOffendingLevelListIDsIndividually.name: Auto-Kick from Level Lists whose IDs Contain Both Of The Two Digits Individually
noOffendingLevelListIDsIndividually.description:
Prevents you from viewing level lists whose Level IDs contain both of The Two Digits, but not consecutively. Notable examples include:
- <cr>harvard entry exam</c> by Perox8
- <cr>DORABAE Remake Trend 2022</c> by robotchief
- <co>The best farming list</c> by OmegaT
- <cr>this weather SUCKS</c> by CLIQUE
- <cr>SUPER NLW RAINBOW</c> by PikachuFan42
- <ca>Eurovision Song Contest</c> by 4y4

noOffendingLevelListIDsExclusiveOr.name: Auto-Kick from Level Lists whose IDs Contain Either Of The Two Digits
noOffendingLevelListIDsExclusiveOr.description:
Prevents you from viewing level lists whose Level IDs contain ***__ONLY__*** one of The Two Digits. Notable examples include:
- <cr>2 Player Training</c> by ZackTheMinion
- <ca>Neodesign Bangers</c> by procurador
- <cl>Sea Creatures</c> by zaroren
- <cr>3</c> by KrmaL
- <cy>Chill Dash</c> by CreatorCreepy

noLevelListsWithOffendingLevelClaimRequi.name: Auto-Kick from Level Lists whose Completion Requirement Count Contains Either Of The Two Digits

noLevelListsWithOffendingRewardCounts.name: Auto-Kick from Level Lists whose Diamond Rewards Count Contains Either Of The Two Digits

irritating-header.name: Irritating Settings
irritating-header.description: These settings might give you a slightly more painful headache. They're enabled by default, but you should probably disable them after some time.

handleXPositionBy.name: Handle X Position By...
handleXPositionBy.description:
Decide what to do if the X position contains The Two Digits.

<c-ff0000>***__THIS SETTING APPLIES TO BOTH PLAYERS. THIS SETTING CAN MAKE SOME LEVELS IMPOSSIBLE IF NOT DISABLED.__***</c>

handleYPositionBy.name: Handle Y Position By...
handleYPositionBy.description:
Decide what to do if the Y position contains The Two Digits.

<c-ff0000>***__THIS SETTING APPLIES TO BOTH PLAYERS. THIS SETTING CAN MAKE SOME LEVELS IMPOSSIBLE IF NOT DISABLED.__***</c>

autoKillOnPercent.name: (Classic) Auto-Kill if Percentage Contains Both Of The Two Digits Consecutively
autoKillOnPercent.description: For obvious reasons, this only applies to Classic levels.

autoKillOnTime.name: (Plat.) Auto-Kill if Time Contains Both Of The Two Digits Consecutively
autoKillOnTime.description: For obvious reasons, this only applies to Platformer levels.

closeProfilesForID.name: Auto-Close Profiles If Account ID Contains Both Of The Two Digits Consecutively

closeProfilesForUserID.name: Auto-Close Profiles If User ID Contains Both Of The Two Digits Consecutively

closeProfilesForGlobalRank.name: Auto-Close Profiles If Global Rank Contains Both Of The Two Digits Consecutively

closeProfilesForAnyStats.name: Auto-Close Profiles If Any Stats Contain Both Of The Two Digits Consecutively

closeProfilesForUsername.name: Auto-Close Profiles If Username References The Two Digits

closeIconKitForStats.name: Auto-Close Icon Kit/Garage If Any Stats Contain Either Of The Two Digits Individually

infuriating-header.name: Infuriating Settings
infuriating-header.description: You ***__really__*** shouldn't enable these settings. They're disabled by default.

noObjectIDs.name: Auto-Kick from Levels Using Object IDs Containing The Two Digits Consecutively

noGroupIDs.name: Auto-Kick from Levels Using Group IDs Containing The Two Digits Consecutively

noEditorLayers.name: Auto-Kick from Levels Using Editor Layers Containing The Two Digits Consecutively

noColorChannels.name: Auto-Kick from Levels Using Color Channels Containing The Two Digits Consecutively

replaceAllText.name: Aggressive Text Replacement
replaceAllText.description: Replaces most instances of The Two Digits with `*` s.
